OL,6,FHer 1943 radio series Wrapped In
OL,7,FVelvet made her one of first black
OL,8,Fartists to regularly broadcast with
OL,9,Fthe BBC.
OL,11,FDuring the Second World War, she
OL,12,Fworked for the Entertainments National
OL,13,FService Association (Ensa) and she
OL,14,Fperformed in air raid shelters and
OL,15,Fhospitals, before becoming one of the
OL,16,Ffirst artists into Germany after the
OL,17,Fliberation.
